            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Hd1e108">Rubrica 1</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De religione et superstitione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e114">
               
               PRime partis mo
               ralis compendii.
               Liber primus in
               cipit: tractans de
               religione et perti
               nentibus ad religio
               nem sub infrascri
               ptis quadraginta
               duobus titulis. 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e140">
               <lb ed="#P"/>de religione et superstitione capitulum 
               <lb ed="#P"/>primum
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e147">
               <lb ed="#P"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Rd1e144">Tullius de natura deorum libro i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Qd1e151">Sanctitas est scientia 
               co<lb ed="#P" break="no"/>lendorum deorum</quote>
            </p>
           <lb ed="#P"/> <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e158"> ¶<ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Rd1e157">Idem rethori
                   corum artis veteris lib. 2. c. 9.</ref> 
                   <lb ed="#P"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Qd1e160">Religio est virtus que superioris cuiusdam nature
                   <lb ed="#P"/> quam diuinam notant curam: cerimoniamque affert.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e170">
              <lb ed="#P"/> ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Rd1e172">Seneca declamationum lib. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Qd1e174">Fortuna
                <lb ed="#P"/>  quos miseros facit: etiam superstitiosos facit </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e180">
              <lb ed="#P"/> ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Rd1e186">Ualerius maximus: lib. 3 ti. de institutis <!--not sure of were to call the line break here so i'm making my best guess, it also seems that there is textual difference here-->
                  antiquis:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Qd1e184">Maxilia ciuitas omnibus qui per ali
                  quam religionis simulationem alimenta inertie
                  querunt: clausas portas habet: mendacem et fu
                  cosam superstitionem submouendam esse existimans</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-d1e196">
               <lb ed="#P"/>  ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Rd1e205"> Cecilius firmianus de beata vita: li. 3.</ref> 
              <lb ed="#P"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d1e400-Qd1e200">Peccati conscientia et metus pene religiosiorem
              <lb ed="#P"/>  facit.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
